com.github.detro.browsermobproxyclient
Class BMPCLocalLauncher

java.lang.Object
  com.github.detro.browsermobproxyclient.BMPCLocalLauncher

public class BMPCLocalLauncher
extends java.lang.Object

Utility class that takes care of Starting and Stopping a Local BrowserMob Proxy.

"Local" means that it's located inside the Current User directory, inside .browsermob-proxy-client/browsermob-proxy-local.

A version of BrowserMob Proxy is contained within the resources of this library. This class takes care of installing/uninstalling (zip/delete) it.

NOTE: Only one Local BrowserMob Proxy running per host is supported, as this is how BrowserMob Proxy is designed to work. Launching more then one will be ignored in the current implementation.

public static void start()
Start Local BrowserMob Proxy. It will also install it if not installed yet. In case client code doesn't, the BrowserMob Proxy process will be shutdown with the JVM (i.e. Runtime Shutdown Hook).
